claims:
1. A system for flight control of an electric vertical takeoff and landing (eVTOL) aircraft, the system comprising:
a pusher component attached to the eVTOL aircraft;
a lift component attached to the eVTOL aircraft;
a pilot override switch, wherein the pilot override switch is operable by a pilot of the eVTOL aircraft and is configured to alter control of the eVTOL aircraft; and
a flight controller communicatively connected to the pilot override switch, wherein the flight controller is configured to:
identify a flight transition point;
initiate operation of the pusher component as a function of the flight transition point;
initiate termination of operation of the lift component;
receive a pilot override signal from the pilot override switch;
generate an autonomous function as a function of a machine-learning model, wherein generating the autonomous function further comprises:
inputting at least a flight element to the machine-learning model, wherein the at least a flight element comprises at least one of a forward thrust datum and an upward thrust datum of the eVTOL aircraft;
inputting the pilot override signal to the machine-learning model; and
outputting the autonomous function as a function of the at least a flight element and the pilot override signal; and

allow, as a function of the autonomous function, the pilot to regain at least partial control over operation of the pusher component and the lift component.

10. A method for flight control of an electric vertical takeoff and landing (eVTOL) aircraft, the method comprising:
identifying, by a flight controller incorporated in an eVTOL aircraft, a flight transition point;
initiating, by the flight controller, operation of a pusher component mechanically coupled to the eVTOL aircraft as a function of the flight transition point;
initiating, by the flight controller, termination of operation of a lift component mechanically coupled to the eVTOL aircraft;
receiving, by the flight controller, a pilot override signal from a pilot override switch communicatively connected to the flight controller, wherein the pilot override switch is operable by a pilot of the eVTOL aircraft and is configured to alter control of the eVTOL aircraft;
generating, by the flight controller, an autonomous function as a function of a machine-learning model, wherein generating the autonomous function further comprises:
inputting at least a flight element to the machine-learning model, wherein the at least a flight element comprises at least one of a forward thrust datum and an upward thrust datum of the eVTOL aircraft;
inputting the pilot override signal to the machine-learning model; and
outputting the autonomous function as a function of the at least a flight element and the pilot override signal; and

allowing, by the flight controller, as a function of the autonomous function, the pilot to regain at least partial control over operation of the pusher component and the lift component.
